msgid "WHAT IS BITCOIN? - The Currency"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:4
msgid "bitcoindesigned.com"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:6
msgid "breaking in pieces"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:8
msgid "Digital Currency"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:10
msgid ""
"It’s all about ones and zeros, meaning it has no physical form such as a "
"coin."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:12
msgid "Cryptocurrency"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:14
msgid ""
"Based on mathematics and cryptography. Which means it can’t be counterfeit - "
"math doesn’t lie."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:16
msgid "limited amount"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:18
msgid ""
"There is a limit of roughly 21 million bitcoins to be ever put in "
"circulation."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:20
msgid ""
"It doesn’t allow anyone to print more bitcoins recklessly, which preserves "
"the currency value - it’s scarce."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:22
msgid "ownership records"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:24
msgid ""
"Bitcoin ownership is actually a record on the Blockchain - this big "
"decentralized ledger - saying those bitcoins were transferred to you."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:26
msgid "mining"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:28
msgid ""
"It’s a type of math problem that needs a lot of processing power. It’s used "
"for writing transactions and those who do it are rewarded with transaction "
"fees and new bitcoins, which is how the currency is issued."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:30
msgid "divisibility"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:32
msgid ""
"The smallest unit of Bitcoin is a Satoshi; it represents one hundred "
"millionth of a bitcoin. But, if needed, this part can become even smaller."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:34
msgid "the features"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:36
msgid "or... Why everyone is so crazy about it"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:38
msgid "Critical (break these and Bitcoin will never be the same)"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:40
msgid "Decentralized"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:42
msgid ""
"No central bank can freeze your accounts or implement poorly conceived "
"policies that devalue your currency."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:44
msgid "No Red-Tape"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:46
msgid "Anyone can use bitcoin, no questions, no documents and no custody fees."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:48
msgid "Pretty Anonymous"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:50
msgid ""
"Your name isn’t linked to your transactions, making it a lot more private "
"and safe than regular bank operations and credit card payments."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:52
msgid "Non-repudiable"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:54
msgid ""
"Once a bitcoin transaction is confirmed, it can’t be reverted unless there "
"is a voluntary agreement between the two parties - such as a store policy."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:56
msgid "Transparent"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:58
msgid ""
"Everyone can check every address and its transactions - although you don’t "
"know the owners of all addresses, only those identities that were entrusted "
"to you."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:60
msgid "changeable (market development might change these a little)"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:62
msgid "Fast"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:64
msgid "Transactions can reach anyone in any part of the world within minutes."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:66
msgctxt "source-text.txt:66"
msgid "Possible Change"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:68
msgid ""
"If the volume of transactions grows  a lot  - say, bitcoin becoming "
"mainstream - transactions will take longer to be cleared on the blockchain."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:70
msgctxt "source-text.txt:70"
msgid "What Might Happen"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:72
msgid ""
"Besides measures to scale Bitcoin’s core, small and quick transactions will "
"probably be cleared by third parties or other layers over the blockchain."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:74
msgid "Cheap"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:76
msgid ""
"Transaction fees are low - currently around 1 USD if you don’t want to wait "
"too much for a confirmation."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:78
msgctxt "source-text.txt:78"
msgid "Possible Change"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:80
msgid ""
"When bitcoin issuing diminishes, the miner’s reward will come mostly from "
"transaction fees, which will be higher."
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:82
msgctxt "source-text.txt:82"
msgid "What Might Happen"
msgstr ""

#: source-text.txt:84
msgid ""
"Predictive calculations indicate that fees will still be very afordable, "
"even when covering all miners expenses alone."
msgstr ""

